USA: United Airlines passenger trapped in lavatory – plane rerouted
Due to a passenger getting trapped in the lavatory a United Airlines flight has been rerouted. During flight 1554 from Washington to San Francisco the toilet door was jammed, the airline told US media.
During an unscheduled layover in Denver on Wednesday afternoon (MDT) the woman was finally released from the tight cabin. According to other passengers, US media wrote, she was trapped for about an hour. For the continuation of the flight to San Francisco the passenger had to change planes.
