The German travel business Thomas Cook cancelled all trips up to and including October 31st, 2019, one day after filing for insolvency. Travels “can not be started due to bankruptcy law concerns”, the company informed on Thursday evening.
Affected by this are bookings through brands like Thomas Cook Signature, Thomas Cook Signature Finest Selection, Neckermann Reisen, ÖGER TOURS, Bucher Reisen, and Air Marin, which are either partly or fully paid for. The company did not give a statement concerning trips starting on November 1st, 2019 or later. Further actions are being examined in accordance with the insolvency insurance, it said.
